<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> make a business of something • make it one’s business</xh5><p> <i>make a business of something—</i>make smth. one’s profession: If you like to travel, you could <u>make a business of</u> transporting other people’s cars to Florida.</p><p><i>make it one’s business—</i>consider smth. one’s duty or responsibility: Miss Leatheran had thereupon <u>made it her business</u> to find out exactly what this foreigner was doing in their midst.</p> </entry>
